#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"These errors can be quite troublesome. However, once you find them, what do you\n"
"do? The following sections will look at two important tools for handling run\n"
"time errors. After that, we'll take a look at compile errors, and how to handle\n"
"them. Let's start out with the first tool for debugging run time errors --\n"
"<c>gdb</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "Debugging using GDB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:108
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"GDB, or the (G)NU (D)e(B)ugger, is a program used to find run time errors that\n"
"normally involve memory corruption. First off, let's take a look at what\n"
"debugging entails. One of the main things you must do in order to debug a\n"
"program is to <c>emerge</c> the program with <c>FEATURES=\"nostrip\"</c>. This\n"
"prevents the stripping of debug symbols. Why are programs stripped by default?\n"
"The reason is the same as that for having gzipped man pages -- saving space.\n"
"Here's how the size of a program varies with and without debug symbol stripping.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filesize Comparison"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:118
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(debug symbols stripped)</comment>\n"
"-rwxr-xr-x  1 chris users 3140  6/28 13:11 bad_code\n"
"<comment>(debug symbols intact)</comment>\n"
"-rwxr-xr-x  1 chris users 6374  6/28 13:10 bad_code\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:125
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Just for reference, <e>bad_code</e> is the program we'll be debugging with\n"
"<c>gdb</c> later on. As you can see, the program without debugging symbols is\n"
"3140 bytes, while the program with them is 6374 bytes. That's close to double\n"
"the size! Two more things can be done for debugging. The first is adding\n"
"<c>ggdb</c> to your CFLAGS and CXXFLAGS. This flag adds more debugging\n"
"information than is generally included. We'll see what that means later on. This\n"
"is how <path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path> <e>might</e> look with the newly added flags.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "make.conf settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:135
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"CFLAGS=\"-O1 -pipe -ggdb\"\n"
"CXXFLAGS=\"${CFLAGS}\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Lastly, you can also add debug to the package's USE flags. This can be done\n"
"with the <path>package.use</path> file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:144
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using package.use to add debug USE flag"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>echo \"category/package debug\" >> /etc/portage/package.use</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:149
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The directory <path>/etc/portage</path> does not exist by default and you may\n"
"have to create it, if you have not already done so. If the package already has\n"
"USE flags set in <path>package.use</path>, you will need to manually modify them\n"
"in your favorite editor.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:156
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Then we re-emerge the package with the modifications we've done so far as shown\n"
"below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:160
#, no-wrap
msgid "Re-emergeing a package with debugging"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>FEATURES=\"nostrip\" emerge package</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now that debug symbols are setup, we can continue with debugging the program.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:171
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running the program with GDB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Let's say we have a program here called \"bad_code\". Some person claims that the\n"
"program crashes and provides an example. You go ahead and test it out:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:179
#, no-wrap
msgid "Breaking The Program"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It seems this person was right. Since the program is obviously broken, we have\n"
"a bug at hand. Now, it's time to use <c>gdb</c> to help solve this matter. First\n"
"we run <c>gdb</c> with <c>--args</c>, then give it the full program with\n"
"arguments like shown:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running Our Program Through GDB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:192
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>gdb --args ./bad_code `perl -e 'print \"A\"x100'`</i>\n"
"GNU gdb 6.3\n"
"Copyright 2004 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\n"
"GDB is free software, covered by the GNU General Public License, and you are\n"
"welcome to change it and/or distribute copies of it under certain conditions.\n"
"Type \"show copying\" to see the conditions.\n"
"There is absolutely no warranty for GDB. Type \"show warranty\" for details.\n"
"This GDB was configured as \"i686-pc-linux-gnu\"...Using host libthread_db library \"/lib/libthread_db.so.1\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:203
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"One can also debug with core dumps. These core files contain the same\n"
"information that the program would produce when run with gdb. In order to debug\n"
"with a core file with bad_code, you would run <c>gdb ./bad_code core</c> where\n"
"core is the name of the core file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:210
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You should see a prompt that says \"(gdb)\" and waits for input. First, we have to\n"
"run the program. We type in <c>run</c> at the command and receive a notice like:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:214
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running the program in GDB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(gdb) <i>run</i>\n"
"Starting program: /home/chris/bad_code\n"
"\n"
"Program received signal SIGSEGV, Segmentation fault.\n"
"0xb7ec6dc0 in strcpy () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:223
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Here we see the program starting, as well as a notification of SIGSEGV, or\n"
"Segmentation Fault. This is GDB telling us that our program has crashed. It\n"
"also gives the last run function it could trace when the program crashes.\n"
"However, this isn't too useful, as there could be multiple strcpy's in the\n"
"program, making it hard for developers to find which one is causing the issue.\n"
"In order to help them out, we do what's called a backtrace. A backtrace runs\n"
"backwards through all the functions that occurred upon program execution, to the\n"
"function at fault. Functions that return (without causing a crash) will not show\n"
"up on the backtrace. To get a backtrace, at the (gdb) prompt, type in <c>bt</c>.\n"
"You will get something like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:235
#, no-wrap
msgid "Program backtrace"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:236
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(gdb) <i>bt</i>\n"
"#0  0xb7ec6dc0 in strcpy () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#1  0x0804838c in run_it ()\n"
"#2  0x080483ba in main ()\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:243
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can notice the trace pattern clearly. main() is called first, followed by\n"
"run_it(), and somewhere in run_it() lies the strcpy() at fault. Things such as\n"
"this help developers narrow down problems. There are a few exceptions to the\n"
"output. First off is forgetting to enable debug symbols with\n"
"<c>FEATURES=\"nostrip\"</c>. With debug symbols stripped, the output looks something\n"
"like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "Program backtrace With debug symbols stripped"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:252
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(gdb) <i>bt</i>\n"
"#0  0xb7e2cdc0 in strcpy () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#1  0x0804838c in ?? ()\n"
"#2  0xbfd19510 in ?? ()\n"
"#3  0x00000000 in ?? ()\n"
"#4  0x00000000 in ?? ()\n"
"#5  0xb7eef148 in libgcc_s_personality () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#6  0x080482ed in ?? ()\n"
"#7  0x080495b0 in ?? ()\n"
"#8  0xbfd19528 in ?? ()\n"
"#9  0xb7dd73b8 in __guard_setup () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#10 0xb7dd742d in __guard_setup () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#11 0x00000006 in ?? ()\n"
"#12 0xbfd19548 in ?? ()\n"
"#13 0x080483ba in ?? ()\n"
"#14 0x00000000 in ?? ()\n"
"#15 0x00000000 in ?? ()\n"
"#16 0xb7deebcc in __new_exitfn () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#17 0x00000000 in ?? ()\n"
"#18 0xbfd19560 in ?? ()\n"
"#19 0xb7ef017c in nullserv () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#20 0xb7dd6f37 in __libc_start_main () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#21 0x00000001 in ?? ()\n"
"#22 0xbfd195d4 in ?? ()\n"
"#23 0xbfd195dc in ?? ()\n"
"#24 0x08048201 in ?? ()\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:281
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This backtrace contains a large number of ?? marks. This is because without\n"
"debug symbols, <c>gdb</c> doesn't know how the program was run. Hence, it is\n"
"crucial that debug symbols are <e>not</e> stripped. Now remember a while ago we\n"
"mentioned the -ggdb flag. Let's see what the output looks like with the flag\n"
"enabled:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "Program backtrace with -ggdb"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:289
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(gdb) <i>bt</i>\n"
"#0  0xb7e4bdc0 in strcpy () from /lib/libc.so.6\n"
"#1  0x0804838c in run_it (input=0x0) at bad_code.c:7\n"
"#2  0x080483ba in main (argc=1, argv=0xbfd3a434) at bad_code.c:12\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:296
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Here we see that a lot more information is available for developers. Not only is\n"
"function information displayed, but even the exact line numbers of the source\n"
"files. This method is the most preferred if you can spare the extra space.\n"
"Here's how much the file size varies between debug, strip, and -ggdb enabled\n"
"programs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:303
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filesize differences With -ggdb flag"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:304
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(debug symbols stripped)</comment>\n"
"-rwxr-xr-x  1 chris users 3140  6/28 13:11 bad_code\n"
"<comment>(debug symbols enabled)</comment>\n"
"-rwxr-xr-x  1 chris users 6374  6/28 13:10 bad_code\n"
"<comment>(-ggdb flag enabled)</comment>\n"
"-rwxr-xr-x  1 chris users 19552  6/28 13:11 bad_code\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:313
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As you can see, -ggdb adds about <e>13178</e> more bytes to the file size over\n"
"the one with debugging symbols. However, as shown above, this increase in file\n"
"size can be worth it if presenting debug information to developers. The\n"
"backtrace can be saved to a file by copying and pasting from the terminal (if\n"
"it's a non-x based terminal, you can use gpm. To keep this doc simple, I\n"
"recommend you read up on the <uri link=\"/doc/en/gpm.xml#doc_chap4\">documentation\n"
"for gpm</uri> to see how to copy and paste with it). Now that we're done with\n"
"<c>gdb</c>, we can quit.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quitting GDB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:324
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(gdb) <i>quit</i>\n"
"The program is running. Exit anyway? (y or n) <i>y</i>\n"
"$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:330
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This ends the walk-through of <c>gdb</c>. Using <c>gdb</c>, we hope that you\n"
"will be able to use it to create better bug reports. However, there are other\n"
"types of errors that can cause a program to fail during run time. One of the\n"
"other ways is through improper file access. We can find those using a nifty\n"
"little tool called <c>strace</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:342
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finding file access errors using strace"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:348
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Programs often use files to fetch configuration information, access hardware or\n"
"write logs. Sometimes, a program attempts to reach such files incorrectly. A\n"
"tool called <c>strace</c> was created to help deal with this. <c>strace</c>\n"
"traces system calls (hence the name) which include calls that use the memory and\n"
"files. For our example, we're going to take a program foobar2. This is an\n"
"updated version of foobar. However, during the change over to foobar2, you\n"
"notice all your configurations are missing!  In foobar version 1, you had it\n"
"setup to say \"foo\", but now it's using the default \"bar\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:358
#, no-wrap
msgid "Foobar2 With an invalid configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:359
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>./foobar2</i>\n"
"Configuration says: bar\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Our previous configuration specifically had it set to foo, so let's use\n"
"<c>strace</c> to find out what's going on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:371
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using strace to track the issue"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:375
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We make <c>strace</c> log the results of the system calls. To do this, we run\n"
"<c>strace</c> with the -o[file] arguments. Let's use it on foobar2 as shown.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running foobar2 through strace"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>strace -ostrace.log ./foobar2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:384
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This creates a file called <path>strace.log</path> in the current directory. We\n"
"check the file, and shown below are the relevant parts from the file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:388
#, no-wrap
msgid "A Look At the strace Log"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:389
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"open(\".foobar2/config\", O_RDONLY)       = 3\n"
"read(3, \"bar\", 3)                       = 3\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:394
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Aha! So There's the problem. Someone moved the configuration directory to\n"
"<path>.foobar2</path> instead of <path>.foobar</path>. We also see the program\n"
"reading in \"bar\" as it should. In this case, we can recommend the ebuild\n"
"maintainer to put a warning about it. For now though, we can copy over the\n"
"config file from <path>.foobar</path> and modify it to produce the correct\n"
"results.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:405 en/bugzilla-howto.xml:740
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1456
#, no-wrap
msgid "Conclusion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:409
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now we've taken care of finding run time bugs. These bugs prove to be\n"
"problematic when you try and run your programs. However, run time errors are\n"
"the least of your concerns if your program won't compile at all. Let's take a\n"
"look at how to address <c>emerge</c> compile errors.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:420
#, no-wrap
msgid "Handling emerge Errors"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:426
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>emerge</c> errors, such as the one displayed earlier, can be a major cause\n"
"of frustration for users. Reporting them is considered crucial for maintaining\n"
"the health of Gentoo. Let's take a look at a sample ebuild, foobar2, which\n"
"contains some build errors.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:435
#, no-wrap
msgid "Evaluating emerge Errors"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:439
#, no-wrap
msgid "Let's take a look at this very simple <c>emerge</c> error:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:442
#, no-wrap
msgid "emerge Error (long lines are manually wrapped to fit the window)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:443
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gcc -D__TEST__ -D__GNU__ -D__LINUX__ -L/usr/lib -I/usr/include -L/usr/lib/nspr/ -I/usr/include/fmod \\\n"
" -c -o foobar2-7.o foobar2-7.c\n"
"gcc -D__TEST__ -D__GNU__ -D__LINUX__ -L/usr/lib -I/usr/include -L/usr/lib/nspr/ -I/usr/include/fmod \\\n"
" -c -o foobar2-8.o foobar2-8.c\n"
"gcc -D__TEST__ -D__GNU__ -D__LINUX__ -L/usr/lib -I/usr/include -L/usr/lib/nspr/ -I/usr/include/fmod \\\n"
" -c -o foobar2-9.o foobar2-9.c\n"
"gcc -D__TEST__ -D__GNU__ -D__LINUX__ -L/usr/lib -I/usr/include -L/usr/lib/nspr/ -I/usr/include/fmod \\\n"
" -c -o foobar2.o foobar2.c\n"
"foobar2.c:1:17: ogg.h: No such file or directory\n"
"make: *** [foobar2.o] Error 1\n"
"\n"
"!!! ERROR: sys-apps/foobar2-1.0 failed.\n"
"!!! Function src_compile, Line 19, Exitcode 2\n"
"!!! Make failed!\n"
"!!! If you need support, post the topmost build error, NOT this status message\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:461
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The program is compiling smoothly when it suddenly stops and presents an error\n"
"message. This particular error can be split into 3 different sections, The\n"
"compile messages, the build error, and the emerge error message as shown below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:466
#, no-wrap
msgid "Parts of the error (long lines are manually wrapped to fit the window)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:467
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Compilation Messages)</comment>\n"
"gcc -D__TEST__ -D__GNU__ -D__LINUX__ -L/usr/lib -I/usr/include -L/usr/lib/nspr/ -I/usr/include/fmod \\\n"
" -c -o foobar2-7.o foobar2-7.c\n"
"gcc -D__TEST__ -D__GNU__ -D__LINUX__ -L/usr/lib -I/usr/include -L/usr/lib/nspr/ -I/usr/include/fmod \\\n"
" -c -o foobar2-8.o foobar2-8.c\n"
"gcc -D__TEST__ -D__GNU__ -D__LINUX__ -L/usr/lib -I/usr/include -L/usr/lib/nspr/ -I/usr/include/fmod \\\n"
" -c -o foobar2-9.o foobar2-9.c\n"
"gcc -D__TEST__ -D__GNU__ -D__LINUX__ -L/usr/lib -I/usr/include -L/usr/lib/nspr/ -I/usr/include/fmod \\\n"
" -c -o foobar2.o foobar2.c\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Build Error)</comment>\n"
"foobar2.c:1:17: ogg.h: No such file or directory\n"
"make: *** [foobar2.o] Error 1\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(emerge Error)</comment>\n"
"!!! ERROR: sys-apps/foobar2-1.0 failed.\n"
"!!! Function src_compile, Line 19, Exitcode 2\n"
"!!! Make failed!\n"
"!!! If you need support, post the topmost build error, NOT this status message\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:489
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The compilation messages are what lead up to the error. Most often, it's good to\n"
"at least include 10 lines of compile information so that the developer knows\n"
"where the compilation was at when the error occurred.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:495
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Please make sure you always include error messages in English, even when your\n"
"system language is set to something else. You can temporarily switch to English\n"
"locale by prepending <c>LC_ALL=C</c> to the emerge command like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:500
#, no-wrap
msgid "Temporarily switching locale to English"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:501
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>LC_ALL=C emerge sys-apps/foobar2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:505
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is also about the only time you should use the <c>LC_ALL</c> environmental\n"
"variable for specifying locale settings. If you are looking for a way to switch\n"
"your system's language, then please consult our <uri\n"
"link=\"guide-localization.xml\">Localization Guide</uri> instead.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:512
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Make errors are the actual error and the information the developer needs. When\n"
"you see \"make: ***\", this is often where the error has occurred. Normally, you\n"
"can copy and paste 10 lines above it and the developer will be able to address\n"
"the issue. However, this may not always work and we'll take a look at an\n"
"alternative shortly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:520
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The emerge error is what <c>emerge</c> throws out as an error. Sometimes, this\n"
"might also contain some important information. Often people make the mistake of\n"
"posting the emerge error and that's all. This is useless by itself, but with\n"
"make error and compile information, a developer can get what application and\n"
"what version of the package is failing. As a side note, make is commonly used as\n"
"the build process for programs (<b>but not always</b>). If you can't find a\n"
"\"make: ***\" error anywhere, then simply copy and paste 20 lines before the\n"
"emerge error. This should take care of most all build system error messages. Now\n"
"let's say the errors seem to be quite large. 10 lines won't be enough to catch\n"
"everything. That's where PORT_LOGDIR comes into play.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:535
#, no-wrap
msgid "emerge and PORT_LOGDIR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:539
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"PORT_LOGDIR is a portage variable that sets up a log directory for separate\n"
"emerge logs. Let's take a look and see what that entails. First, run your\n"
"emerge with PORT_LOGDIR set to your favorite log location. Let's say we have a\n"
"location <path>/var/log/portage</path>. We'll use that for our log directory:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:546
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the default setup, <path>/var/log/portage</path> does not exist, and you will\n"
"most likely have to create it. If you do not, portage will fail to write the\n"
"logs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:551
#, no-wrap
msgid "emerge-ing With PORT_LOGDIR"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:552
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>PORT_LOGDIR=/var/log/portage emerge cate-gory/foobar2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:556
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now the emerge fails again. However, this time we have a log we can work with,\n"
"and attach to the bug later on. Let's take a quick look at our log directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:560
#, no-wrap
msgid "PORT_LOGDIR Contents"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:561
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>ls -la /var/log/portage</i>\n"
"total 16\n"
"drwxrws---   2 root root 4096 Jun 30 10:08 .\n"
"drwxr-xr-x  15 root root 4096 Jun 30 10:08 ..\n"
"-rw-r--r--   1 root root 7390 Jun 30 10:09 cate-gory:foobar2-1.0:20090110-213217.log\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:569
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The log files have the format [category]:[package name]-[version]:[date].log. A\n"
"quick look at the log file will show the entire emerge process. This can be\n"
"attached later on as we'll see in the bug reporting section. Now that we've\n"
"safely obtained our information needed to report the bug we can continue to do\n"
"so. However, before we get started on that, we need to make sure no one else\n"
"has reported the issue. Let's take a look at searching for bugs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:582
#, no-wrap
msgid "Searching Using Bugzilla"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:588
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<uri link=\"http://www.bugzilla.org\">Bugzilla</uri> is what we at Gentoo use to\n"
"handle bugs. Gentoo's Bugzilla is reachable by HTTPS and HTTP. HTTPS is\n"
"available for those on insecure networks or simply paranoid :). For the sake of\n"
"consistency, we will be using the HTTPS version in the examples to follow. Head\n"
"over to <uri link=\"https://bugs.gentoo.org\">Gentoo Bugs</uri> to see how it\n"
"looks.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:597
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"One of the most frustrating things for developers and bug-wranglers is finding\n"
"duplicate bug reports. These cost them valuable time that they could otherwise\n"
"use to work on more important bugs. Often, this can be prevented by a few simple\n"
"search methods. So we're going to see how to search for bugs and find out if\n"
"you have one that's similar. For this example, we're going to use the xclass\n"
"emerge error that was used earlier.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:605
#, no-wrap
msgid "xclass emerge error"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:636
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"So to begin searching, we head over to the <uri\n"
"link=\"https://bugs.gentoo.org/\">Bugzilla Homepage</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:640 en/bugzilla-howto.xml:764
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bugzilla Homepage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:643
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We'll click on \"Query Existing bug reports\". The reason why we choose this\n"
"over the basic bug search is because the basic bug search tends to give vague\n"
"results and often hinders users from looking through the results and finding the\n"
"duplicate bug. Once we click on the query screen, we reach the next page:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:649
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bugzilla Search Page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:652
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you've used the Advanced Search before, you'll most likely see that screen\n"
"instead.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:657
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Proceed by clicking on the \"Advanced Search\" link to bring up the Advanced\n"
"Search page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:661
#, no-wrap
msgid "Advanced Search Page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:664
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is how the Advanced Search Page looks like. While it may seem overwhelming\n"
"at first, we're going to look at a few simple areas to narrow down the rather\n"
"vague searches bugzilla returns.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:669
#, no-wrap
msgid "Content"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:672
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The first field is the summary of the bug. Here we're simply going to put the\n"
"name of the package that's crashing. If bugzie doesn't return results, try\n"
"removing the package name, just in case someone didn't put that in the summary\n"
"(highly unlikely, but we've seen a fair share of strange bug reports).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:679
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Product, Component, and Version should all be set to the default. This\n"
"prevents us from being too specific and missing all the bugs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:684
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Comment is the important part. Use the comment field to list what appears to be\n"
"a specific instance of the error. Basically, don't use anything like the\n"
"beginning of the build error, find a line that's before it stating a true\n"
"error. Also, you'll want to filter out any punctuation to prevent bugzilla\n"
"from interpreting the results the comment the wrong way. Example from the xclass\n"
"emerge error:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:692
#, no-wrap
msgid "Comment Line Content"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:693
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"menudef.h:78: error: brace-enclosed initializer used to initialize `OXPopupMenu'\n"
"<comment>(Remove the quotes ' ')</comment>\n"
"menudef.h 78 error brace-enclosed initializer used to initialize OXPopupMenu\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:699
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The above is specific enough to where we'll find the bug without wading through\n"
"other xclass compile failure candidates.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:704
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"URI, Whiteboard, and Keywords can all be left alone. What we've entered so far\n"
"should be enough to find our bug. Let's take a look at what we have filled out.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:708
#, no-wrap
msgid "Completed Search Form"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:711
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now we click on the Search button and here come the results...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:714
#, no-wrap
msgid "Search Results"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:717
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Only 2 bugs! That's a lot easier to deal with. We click on the first one to\n"
"check, and sure enough it's the one we're looking for.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:721
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bug Located"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:724
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Not only is it the one we want, but it has also been resolved. By checking the\n"
"last comment we see the solution and know what to do in order to resolve it.\n"
"Now, let's see what would have happened if we had not used the advanced search.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:729
#, no-wrap
msgid "Basic Search Results"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:732
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"4 more bugs to deal with! It gets even worse with larger packages. However,\n"
"with these simple tools, we're able to significantly narrow down the search to\n"
"try and locate a specific bug.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:744
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Let's say that you have searched and searched but still can't find a bug.\n"
"You've found yourself a new bug. Let's take a look at the bug reporting process\n"
"for submitting your new bug.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:754
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reporting Bugs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:760
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In this chapter, we'll figure out how to use Bugzilla to file a shiny, new bug.\n"
"Head over to <uri link=\"https://bugs.gentoo.org\">Gentoo Bugs</uri> and...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:767
#, no-wrap
msgid "Click on \"Report a Bug - Using the guided format\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:770
#, no-wrap
msgid "Product Selection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:773
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As you can see, <b>major</b> emphasis has been placed on putting your bug in the\n"
"right place. Gentoo Linux is where a large majority of bugs go.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:778
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Despite this, some people will file ebuild bugs in portage development\n"
"(assumption that portage team handles the portage tree) or infra (assumption\n"
"that infra has access to mirrors and rsync and can fix it directly). This is\n"
"simply not how things work.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:785
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Another common misconception occurs with our Documentation bugs. For example, a\n"
"user finds a bug with the <uri link=\"/proj/en/releng/catalyst/\">Catalyst\n"
"Docs</uri>. The general tendency is to file a bug under Docs-user, which gets\n"
"assigned to the <uri link=\"http://gdp.gentoo.org\">GDP</uri>, when it should\n"
"actually go to a member of the <uri link=\"/proj/en/releng/\">Release\n"
"Engineering</uri> team. As a rule of thumb, only documentation under\n"
"<path>http://www.gentoo.org/doc/*</path> is under the GDP. Anything under\n"
"<path>http://www.gentoo.org/proj/*</path> is under the respective teams.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:796
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We would rather see a bug whose product was not supposed to be Gentoo Linux but\n"
"has been filed under the same rather than seeing a bug which belongs the Gentoo\n"
"Linux product and filed elsewhere. While neither is preferred, the former is\n"
"more acceptable and understandable (except website bugs.. we might have an issue\n"
"with that...).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:804
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Our bug goes in Gentoo Linux as it's an ebuild bug. We head over there and are\n"
"presented with the multi-step bug reporting process. Let us now proceed with\n"
"Step 1...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:809
#, no-wrap
msgid "Guided Format Step 1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:812
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The first step here is really important (as the red text tells you). This is\n"
"where you search to see that someone else hasn't hit the same bug you have, yet.\n"
"If you do skip this step and a bug like yours already exists, it will be marked\n"
"as a DUPLICATE thus wasting a large amount of QA effort. To give you an idea,\n"
"the bug numbers that are struck out above are duplicate bugs. Now comes step 2,\n"
"where we give the information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:823
#, no-wrap
msgid "Required Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:826
#, no-wrap
msgid "Basic Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:829
#, no-wrap
msgid "Let us take a closer look at what's what.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:834
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    First, there's the Product. The product will narrow down the bug to a\n"
"    specific area of Gentoo like Bugzilla (for bugs relating to\n"
"    bugs.gentoo.org), Docs-user(for User Documentation) or Gentoo Linux (for\n"
"    ebuilds and the like).\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:840
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Component is where exactly the problem occurs, more specifically which part\n"
"    of selected product the bug comes under. This makes classification easier.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:844
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Hardware platform is what architecture you're running. If you were running\n"
"    SPARC, you would set it to SPARC.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:848
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Operating System is what Operating System you're using. Because Gentoo is\n"
"    considered a \"Meta-distribution\", it can run on other operating systems\n"
"    beside Linux.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:855
#, no-wrap
msgid "So, for our example bug, we have :\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:859
#, no-wrap
msgid "Product - Gentoo Linux (Since it is an ebuild issue)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:860
#, no-wrap
msgid "Component - Application (It is an application at fault, foobar2)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:861
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hardware Platform - All (This error could occur across architectures)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:862
#, no-wrap
msgid "Operation System - All (It could occur on all types of systems)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:865
#, no-wrap
msgid "Completed Basic Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:869
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Build Identifier is basically the User Agent of the browser that is being\n"
"    used to report the bugs (for logging purposes). You can just leave this as\n"
"    is.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:874
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    URL is optional and is used to point to relevant information on another site\n"
"    (upstream bugzilla, release notes on package homepage etc.). You should\n"
"    never use URL to point to pastebins for error messages, logs, <c>emerge\n"
"    --info</c> output, screenshots or similar information. Instead, these should\n"
"    always be attached to the bug.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:881
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    In the Summary, you should put the package category, name, and number.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:886
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Not including the category in the summary really isn't too bad, but it's\n"
"recommended. If you don't include the package name, however, we won't know what\n"
"you're filling a bug for, and will have to ask you about it later. The version\n"
"number is important for people searching for bugs. If 20 people filed bugs and\n"
"not one put a version number, how would people looking for similar bugs be able\n"
"to tell if one was there's? They'd have to look through every single bug, which\n"
"isn't too hard, but if there are say, 200 bugs.. it's not that easy. After all\n"
"the package information, you'll want to include a small description of the\n"
"incident. Here's an example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:897
#, no-wrap
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:900
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"These simple rules can make handling bugs a lot easier. Next are the details.\n"
"Here we put in the information about the bug. We'll demonstrate with an example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:904
#, no-wrap
msgid "Details"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:907
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now the developer knows why we're filing the bug. They can then try to\n"
"reproduce it. Reproducibility tells us how often we were able to make the\n"
"problem recur. In this example, we can reproduce it any time simply by running\n"
"foobar2. Let's put that information in.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:913
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reproduction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:916
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We have explained how we found the bug. The next step is to explain what were\n"
"the results we got and what we think they should actually be.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:920
#, no-wrap
msgid "Results"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:923
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We could then provide additional information. This could be things such as\n"
"stack traces, <b>sections</b> (since the whole log is usually big and of not\n"
"much use) of strace logs, but most importantly, your <c>emerge --info</c>\n"
"output. Here's an example.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:929
#, no-wrap
msgid "Additional Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:932
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Lastly we select the severity of the bug. Please look this over carefully. In\n"
"most cases it's OK to leave it as is and someone will raise/lower it for you.\n"
"However, if you raise the severity of the bug, please make sure you read it over\n"
"carefully and make sure you're not making a mistake. A run down of the various\n"
"levels is given below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:941
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Blocker - The program just plain doesn't want to emerge or is a major\n"
"    hinderance to the system. For example a <c>baselayout</c> issue which\n"
"    prevents a system from booting up would be a sure candidate to be labelled\n"
"    blocker.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:947
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Critical - The program has loss of data or severe memory leaks during\n"
"    runtime. Again, an important program like say <c>net-tools</c> failing to\n"
"    compile could be labelled critical. It won't prevent the system from\n"
"    starting up, but is quite essential for day to day stuff.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:953
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Major - The program crashes, but nothing that causes your system severe\n"
"    damage or information loss.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:957
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Minor - Your program crashes here and there with apparent workarounds.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:960
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Normal - The default. If you're not sure leave it here unless it's a new\n"
"    build or cosmetic change, then read below for more information.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:963
#, no-wrap
msgid "Trivial - Things such as a mispelled word or whitespace clean up. "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:965
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Enhancement - A request to enable a new feature in a program, or more\n"
"    specifically <e>new ebuilds</e>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:970
#, no-wrap
msgid "Severity"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:973
#, no-wrap
msgid "Here, we'll set it to Normal.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:977
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now we can submit the bug report by clicking on the Submit Bug Report box. You\n"
"will now see your new bug come up. See <uri\n"
"link=\"https://bugs.gentoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=97265\">Bug 97561</uri> for what\n"
"the result looks like. We've reported our bug! Now let's see how it's dealt\n"
"with.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:987
#, no-wrap
msgid "Zero-day bump requests"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:991
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"So far, we've shown what to do when filing a bug. Now let's take a look at what\n"
"<e>not</e> to do.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:996
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Suppose that you've eagerly been following an upstream project's schedule, and\n"
"when you check their homepage, guess what? They just released a new version a\n"
"few minutes ago! Most users would immediately rush over to Gentoo's bugzilla to\n"
"report the new version is available; please bump the existing version and add\n"
"it to Portage, etc. However, this is exactly what you should <b>not</b> do.\n"
"These kinds of requests are called zero-day (or 0-day) bump requests, as they're\n"
"made the same day that a new version is released.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1006
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<b>Please wait <e>at least</e> 48 hours before reporting a new release on our\n"
"bugzilla.</b> Also, you <e>must</e> check bugzilla before posting your request\n"
"to make sure that someone else hasn't already reported it, or that the Gentoo\n"
"maintainers haven't already dealt with the new version.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1013
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Why should you wait? First, it's quite rude to demand that Gentoo developers\n"
"drop everything they're doing just to add a new release that came out 15 minutes\n"
"ago. Your zero-day bump request could be marked as INVALID or LATER, as\n"
"developers have plenty of pressing issues to keep them busy. Second, developers\n"
"are usually aware of pending new releases well in advance of users, as they must\n"
"follow upstream quite closely. They already know a new version is on its way.\n"
"In many cases, they will have already opened a bug, or might even already added\n"
"it in Portage as a masked package.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1024
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Be smart when testing and requesting new versions of packages. Search bugzilla\n"
"before posting your bump request -- is there already a bug open? Have you synced\n"
"lately; is it already in Portage? Has it actually been released by upstream?\n"
"Basic common sense will go a long way, and will endear you to developers that\n"
"already have a lot to do. If it's been several days since release and you're\n"
"sure that there are no open requests for it (and that it's not in Portage), then\n"
"you can open up a new bug. Be sure to mention that it compiles and runs well on\n"
"your arch. Any other helpful information you provide is most welcome.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1035
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Want to see the newest version of your favorite package in Portage? File smart\n"
"bugs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1044
#, no-wrap
msgid "Working With Your Bug"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1049
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Looking at the bug, we see the information we provided earlier. You will notice\n"
"that the bug has been assigned to bug-wranglers@gentoo.org. This is the default\n"
"location for Application component bugs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1054
#, no-wrap
msgid "New Bug Basic Information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1057
#, no-wrap
msgid "The details we entered about the bug are available as well.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1060
#, no-wrap
msgid "New Bug Details"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1063
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"However, bug-wranglers (usually) won't fix our bugs, so we'll reassign it to\n"
"someone that can (you can let bug-wranglers re-assign it for you as well). For\n"
"this we use the package's metadata.xml. You can normally find them in\n"
"<path>/usr/portage/category/package/metadata.xml</path>. Here's one I've made up\n"
"for foobar2.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1071
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You have to be the reporter of the bug or a member of certain Gentoo Bugzilla\n"
"groups (like Gentoo Developers) to be able to reassign bugs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1075
#, no-wrap
msgid "metadata.xml"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1076
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE pkgmetadata SYSTEM \"http://www.gentoo.org/dtd/metadata.dtd\"&gt;\n"
"&lt;pkgmetadata&gt;\n"
"&lt;herd&gt;chriswhite&lt;/herd&gt;\n"
"&lt;maintainer&gt;\n"
"&lt;email&gt;chriswhite@gentoo.org&lt;/email&gt;\n"
"&lt;name&gt;Chris White&lt;/name&gt;\n"
"&lt;/maintainer&gt;\n"
"&lt;longdescription lang=\"en\"&gt;\n"
"Foobar2 is a package that uses a configuration file to display a word.\n"
"&lt;/longdescription&gt;\n"
"&lt;/pkgmetadata&gt;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1091
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Notice the maintainer section. This lists the maintainer of the package, which\n"
"in this case is myself, Chris White. The email listed is chriswhite@gentoo.org.\n"
"We will use this to re-assign the bug to the proper person. To do this, click\n"
"the bubble next to Reassign bug to, then fill in the email.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1098
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A bug for a package without a metadata.xml file should be re-assigned to\n"
"maintainer-needed@gentoo.org and a package that needs a Gentoo Developer to\n"
"maintain should be assigned to maintainer-wanted@gentoo.org.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1103
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bug Reassignment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1106
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Then hit the Commit button for the changes to take place. The bug has been\n"
"reassigned to me. Shortly afterward, you notice (by email usually) that I've\n"
"responded to your bug. I've stated that I'd like to see an strace log to figure\n"
"out how the program is trying to reach your configuration file. You follow the\n"
"previous instructions on using strace and obtain an strace log. Now you need to\n"
"attach it to the bug. In order to do this, click on \"Create A New Attachment\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1114
#, no-wrap
msgid "New Attachment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1117
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now we have to attach the log. Let's go throught it step wise.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1122
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    File - This is the location of the file in your machine. In this example,\n"
"    the location of <path>strace.log</path>. You can use the \"Browse...\" button\n"
"    to select the file, or enter the path directly in the text field.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1127
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Description - A short one liner, or a few wors describing the attachment.\n"
"    We'll just enter strace.log here, since that's quite self-explanatory.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1131
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Content Type - This is the type of the file we're attaching to the bug.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1134
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Obsoletes - If there were attachements submitted to the bug before the\n"
"    current one, you have an option of declaring them obsoleted by yours. Since\n"
"    we have no prior attachments to this bug, we need not bother.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Comment - Enter comments that will be visible along with the attachments.\n"
"    You could elaborate on the attachment here, if needed.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1145
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"With respect to Content Type, here are a few more details. You can check the\n"
"\"patch\" checkbox if you're submitting a patch. Otherwise, you could ask\n"
"Bugzilla to \"auto-detect\" the file type (not advisable). The other options are\n"
"\"select from list\", which is most frequently used. Use plain text (text/plain)\n"
"for <e>most</e> attachments except binary files like images (which can use\n"
"image/gif, image/jpeg or image/png depending on type) or compressed files like\n"
".tar.bz2 which would use application/octet-stream as content type.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1155
#, no-wrap
msgid "New Attachment Completed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1158
#, no-wrap
msgid "We submit <path>strace.log</path> and it is reflected on the bug report.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1161
#, no-wrap
msgid "Attached strace log"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1164
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We've mentioned before that sometimes ebuilds will tell you to attach a file in\n"
"the emerge error. An example can be seen below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1168
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example File Attachment Request"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1169
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"configure: error: PNG support requires ZLIB. Use --with-zlib-dir=&lt;DIR&gt;\n"
"\n"
"!!! Please attach the config.log to your bug report:\n"
"!!! /var/tmp/portage/php-5.0.3-r1/work/php-5.0.3/config.log\n"
"\n"
"!!! ERROR: dev-php/php-5.0.3-r1 failed.\n"
"!!! Function econf, Line 485, Exitcode 0\n"
"!!! econf failed\n"
"!!! If you need support, post the topmost build error, NOT this status message.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1181
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please attach any file mentioned like this to your bug report.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Sometimes a developer might ask you to attach a diff or patch for a file.\n"
"Standard diff files can be obtained through:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1189
#, no-wrap
msgid "Standard Diff Creation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1190
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>cp file file.old</i>\n"
"$ <i>nano file</i>\n"
"$ <i>diff -u file.old file</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1196
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For C/C++ source files, the <b>-p</b> flag is added to show what function calls\n"
"the diff applies to:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1200
#, no-wrap
msgid "Diff-ing C/C++ source"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1201
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ <i>cp file.c file.c.old</i>\n"
"$ <i>nano file.c</i>\n"
"$ <i>diff -up file.c.old file.c</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1207
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The documentation team will require the flag combination <b>-Nt</b> as well as\n"
"<b>-u</b>. This mainly has to do with tab expansion. You can create such a diff\n"
"with:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1212
#, no-wrap
msgid "Documentation diffs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1213
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$<i> cp file.xml file.xml.old</i>\n"
"$<i> nano file.xml</i>\n"
"$<i> diff -Nut file.xml.old file.xml</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1219
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"And your diff is created. While we're doing all this, suppose another person\n"
"finds your bug by searching through bugzilla and is curious to keep track of\n"
"the bug, they may do so by putting their email in the Add CC field of the bug\n"
"as shown below. You could also keep track of other bugs by following the same\n"
"method.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1226
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding Email To CC:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1229
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Email addresses must be registered with Gentoo Bugzilla. In order to CC multiple\n"
"addresses, simply separate them with commas or spaces.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1234
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After all this work, the bug can undergo various status markings. This is\n"
"usually done by the Gentoo Developers and sometimes by the reporter. The\n"
"following are the various possible states a bug may go through during its\n"
"lifetime.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1242
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    UNCONFIRMED - You're generally not going to see this too often. This means\n"
"    that a bug reporter has opened a bug using the advanced method and is\n"
"    uncertain his or her bug is an actual bug.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1246
#, no-wrap
msgid "NEW - Bugs that are first opened are considered new."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1248
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ASSIGNED - When the person you've assigned the bug too validates your bug,\n"
"    it will often receive ASSIGNED status while they figure out the issue.\n"
"    This lets you know that they've accepted your bug as a real bug.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1253
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    REOPENED - Someone has resolved a bug and you think the solution is not\n"
"    feasible or the problem still persists. At this point, you may re-open the\n"
"    bug. Please <b>do not abuse this</b>. If a developer closes the bug a\n"
"    second or third time, chances are that your bug is closed.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1259
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    RESOLVED - A firm decision has been taken on the bug. Usually goes onto\n"
"    FIXED to indicate the bug is solved and the matter closed although various\n"
"    other resolutions are possible. We'll look into those a little later.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1264
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    VERIFIED - The steps take to work the bug are correct. This is usually a QA\n"
"    thing.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1268
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    CLOSED - Basically means RIP for the bug and it's buried under the never\n"
"    ending flow of new bugs.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1274
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now shortly afterward, we find the error in the strace log and fix the bug and\n"
"mark it as RESOLVED FIXED and mention that there was a change in the location\n"
"of configuration files, and that I will update the ebuild with a warning about\n"
"it. The bug now becomes resolved, and you are shown the following.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1280
#, no-wrap
msgid "Resolved Bug"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1283
#, no-wrap
msgid "A little below, you'll see the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1286
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bug Options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1289
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This gives you the option of Reopening the bug if you wish to (i.e. the\n"
"developer thinks it's resolved but it's really not to your standards). Now our\n"
"bug is fixed! However, different resolutions can occur. Here's a small list:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1296
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    FIXED - The bug is fixed, follow the instructions to resolve your issue.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1299
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    INVALID - You did not do something specifically documented, causing the\n"
"    bug.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1302
#, no-wrap
msgid "DUPLICATE - You didn't use this guide and reported a duplicate bug."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1304
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    WORKSFORME - Developer/person assigned the bug cannot reproduce your error.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1307
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    CANTFIX - Somehow the bug cannot be solved because of certain\n"
"    circumstances. These circumstances will be noted by the person taking the\n"
"    bug.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1312
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    WONTFIX - This is usually applied to new ebuilds or feature requests.\n"
"    Basically the developer does not want to add a certain feature because it\n"
"    is not needed, a better alternative exists, or it's just plain broken.\n"
"    Sometimes you may be given a solution to get said issue resolved.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1318
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    UPSTREAM - The bug cannot be fixed by the Gentoo development team, and have\n"
"    requested you take the problem upstream (the people that actually made the\n"
"    program) for review. Upstream has a few ways of handling bugs. These\n"
"    include mailing lists, irc channels, and even bug reporting systems. If\n"
"    you're not sure how to contact them, ask in the bug and someone will point\n"
"    you to the right direction.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1328
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Sometimes, before the bug can be resolved, a developer may request that you\n"
"test an updated ebulid. In the next chapter we'll take a look at testing\n"
"ebuilds.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1338
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing Ebuilds"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1340
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting The Files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1344
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Let's say that you reported a bug for the foobar2 compile fix from earlier. Now\n"
"developers might find out what the problem is and might need you to test the\n"
"ebuild for them to be sure it works for you as well:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><figure>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1349
#, no-wrap
msgid "Ebuild Test Request"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1352
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Some rather confusing vocabulary is used here. First off, let's see what an\n"
"overlay is. An overlay is a special directory like <path>/usr/portage</path>,\n"
"the difference being that when you <c>emerge sync</c>, files contained within it\n"
"will not be deleted. Luckily, a special <path>/usr/local/portage</path>\n"
"directory is created for that purpose. Let's go ahead and set our portage\n"
"overlay in<path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path>. Open make.conf up in your favorite editor\n"
"and add this towards the end.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1361
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting Up PORTDIR_OVERLAY"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1362
#, no-wrap
msgid "PORTDIR_OVERLAY=\"/usr/local/portage\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1366
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now we'll want to create the appropriate directories to put our test ebuild\n"
"files in. In this case, we're supposed to put them in sys-apps/foobar2. You'll\n"
"notice that the second comment asks for a <path>files</path> directory for the\n"
"patch. This directory holds other required files that aren't included with\n"
"the standard source archive (patches, init.d scripts, etc). This is a subdir in\n"
"the package directory called <path>files</path>. Go ahead and create these\n"
"directories:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1375
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting Up The Category And Package Directories"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1376
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>mkdir -p /usr/local/portage/sys-apps/foobar2/files</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1380
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The -p in mkdir creates not only the directory you want but also any missing\n"
"parent directories as well (sys-apps and foobar2 in this case).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1385
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Ok now, we can go ahead and download the files. First, download the ebuild\n"
"into <path>/usr/local/portage/sys-apps/foobar2</path>, and then add the patch\n"
"to <path>/usr/local/portage/sys-apps/foobar2/files</path>. Now that we have the\n"
"files, we can begin working on testing the ebuild.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1394
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing The ebuild"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1398
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The process to create an ebuild that can be used by emerge is fairly simple. You\n"
"must create a Manifest file for the ebuild. This can be done with\n"
"the ebuild command. Run it as shown.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1403
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the Manifest file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1404
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>ebuild foobar2-1.0.ebuild manifest</i>\n"
"&gt;&gt;&gt; Creating Manifest for /usr/local/portage/sys-apps/foobar2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1409
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now let's test to see if it works as it should.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1412
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing With emerge -pv"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1413
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge -pv foobar2</i>\n"
"\n"
"These are the packages that I would merge, in order:\n"
"\n"
"Calculating dependencies ...done!\n"
"[ebuild  N    ] sys-apps/foobar2-1.0  0 kB [1]\n"
"\n"
"Total size of downloads: 0 kB\n"
"Portage overlays:\n"
" [1] /usr/local/portage\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1426
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It does seem to have worked! You'll notice the [1] next to the [ebuild] line.\n"
"That points to <path>/usr/local/portage</path>, which is the overlay we created\n"
"earlier. Now we go ahead and emerge the package.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1431
#, no-wrap
msgid "Emerge Result"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1432
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge foobar2</i>\n"
" Calculating dependencies ...done!\n"
"<comment>(compile info snipped)</comment>\n"
">>> Unpacking foobar2-1.0.tar.bz2 to /var/tmp/portage/foobar2-1.0/work\n"
" * Applying foobar2-1.0-Makefile.patch ...                                    [ ok ]\n"
"<comment>(compile info snipped)</comment>\n"
">>> Merging sys-apps/foobar2-1.0 to /\n"
">>> chris +sandbox(preinst)\n"
"--- /usr/\n"
"--- /usr/bin/\n"
">>> /usr/bin/foobar2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1446
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the first section we see that the emerge started off as it should. The second\n"
"section shows our patch being applied successfully by the \"[ ok ]\" status\n"
"message to the right. The last section tells us the program compiled ok. The\n"
"patch works! Now we can go and let the developer know that their patch works\n"
"fine, and that they can commit the fix to portage.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/bugzilla-howto.xml:1460
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This concludes the howto on working with Bugzilla. I hope you find this useful.\n"
"If you have any questions, comments, or ideas regarding this document, please\n"
"send them to me at <mail>chriswhite@gentoo.org</mail>. Special thanks go to\n"
"moreon for his notes on -g flags and compile errors, the people at #gentoo-bugs\n"
"for helping out with bug-wrangling, Griffon26 for his notes on\n"
"maintainer-needed, robbat2 for general suggestions and fox2mike for fixing up\n"
"the doc and adding stuff as needed.\n"
msgstr ""
